1
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:02,850
Instructor: When you are working

2
00:00:02,850 --> 00:00:04,560
with Entity Framework Core

3
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:06,540
and you are just getting started,

4
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:09,690
it is very common that you might run into some issues

5
00:00:09,690 --> 00:00:10,980
with a migration

6
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:14,550
and some things might not work based on what you expect.

7
00:00:14,550 --> 00:00:16,140
And migrations are something

8
00:00:16,140 --> 00:00:18,405
that are very easy to be corrupted

9
00:00:18,405 --> 00:00:20,463
if you do not pay attention.

10
00:00:21,870 --> 00:00:24,510
You can always roll back a migration.

11
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:27,060
You can make more changes, create a model,

12
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:30,030
add new migration, but for some reason,

13
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:33,240
if everything is corrupt and you want to start fresh

14
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,883
while learning, how do you do that?

15
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,390
Doing that is pretty simple.

16
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:43,530
So let me show you how to do that in this video.

17
00:00:43,530 --> 00:00:46,770
First thing, we will go to SQL Server here

18
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:48,570
and everything is corrupt.

19
00:00:48,570 --> 00:00:53,570
So we will delete the database, which is Bulky right here.

20
00:00:53,610 --> 00:00:54,933
Let's delete that.

21
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:58,080
Next, we will go back here.

22
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,950
Inside the DataAccess, we have Migrations.

23
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:05,910
Now our migrations are corrupt and we want to start fresh.

24
00:01:05,910 --> 00:01:08,643
You can delete the migrations altogether.

25
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,480
Perfect. Now there are no migrations.

26
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,370
There is no database.

27
00:01:14,370 --> 00:01:19,260
To start fresh you can go to Tools Package Manager Console

28
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:21,003
and add a new migration.

29
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:25,860
We know right now we are only adding the category model,

30
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:28,240
so we can say AddCategoryToDb

31
00:01:29,430 --> 00:01:32,793
and we are also seeding the category table.

32
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:37,353
So we will say AddCategoryToDbAndSeedTable.

33
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:43,050
Now when you execute this, you will see an error message.

34
00:01:43,050 --> 00:01:44,220
And there you go.

35
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:47,070
The target project is BulkyWeb.

36
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:51,150
Now we have moved our data to a DataAccess project.

37
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:56,150
So the default project must be updated to DataAccess.

38
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:59,250
So default project will be DataAccess

39
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:02,580
and the default startup project is BulkyWeb.

40
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:07,083
With that configured, if I run this, it will add migration.

41
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:10,860
Now, right now, there were no previous migration.

42
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:14,310
So what it will do is it will identify all the changes

43
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:17,730
that it has to push to a new database.

44
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:21,870
It has to create categories table, it has to insert data,

45
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,033
and that is all we have right now.

46
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:29,250
With that configured, we can hit the command update-database

47
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:32,433
and our database will be populated.

48
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,913
Perfect.

49
00:02:34,913 --> 00:02:37,950
If we go back and refresh the database here,

50
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:41,160
we have Bulky, Tables,

51
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:44,283
and we should have Categories populated.

52
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:46,950
Great.

53
00:02:46,950 --> 00:02:49,200
So the only disadvantage this time

54
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,080
is if you have added some new categories,

55
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:56,013
those will not be available because we are starting fresh.

56
00:02:56,940 --> 00:02:59,310
But basically anytime in the video

57
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:01,050
if your migrations are corrupt

58
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:04,290
and you don't know how to reset your database

59
00:03:04,290 --> 00:03:06,873
this is the video that you should look for.

